        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 2:24AM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 224 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Elbert, or 10 miles southwest of Olney, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Olney around 235 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Padgett and Newcastle.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
north central Texas.</instruction>
